description: From Middle English auncestrie, from Old French ancesserie. See ancestor.

entries.meaning: Condition as to ancestors; ancestral lineage; hence, birth or honorable descent.
examples: Title and ancestry render a good man more illustrious, but an ill one more contemptible. -Addison.

entries.meaning: A series of ancestors or progenitors; lineage, or those who compose the line of natural descent.
